article.description: — Derek St. Hilaire had a season-high 21 points as New Orleans routed Incarnate Word 86-64 on Saturday night.
article.headline: St. Hilaire leads New Orleans past Incarnate Word 86-64
article.linkText: St. Hilaire leads New Orleans past Incarnate Word 86-64
article.story: NEW ORLEANS -- — Derek St. Hilaire had a season-high 21 points as New Orleans routed Incarnate Word 86-64 on Saturday night. St. Hilaire hit 9 of 12 shots. Troy Green had 18 points and seven rebounds for New Orleans (2-9, 1-2 Southland Conference), which snapped its six-game losing streak. Damion Rosser added 18 points and seven rebounds. New Orleans dominated the first half and led 40-25 at the break. The Privateers’ 46 second-half points were a season high for the team. Godsgift Ezedinma had 10 points for the Cardinals (4-5, 1-1). Drew Lutz added seven assists. Keaston Willis, the Cardinals’ leading scorer coming into the contest at 21 points per game, scored eight points (3-of-15 shooting). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
